                                        =======================
                                            COLLECTIONS
                                        =======================

--> collections are used to store group of objects/values
--> collections are growable in nature (dynamically collection size can be increased and decreased based on data )
--> we can store any type of data in Collections (homegeneuous and heterogeneuous)
--> Collections providing predefined methods to insert, update, delete, retrive, sort etc..........
--> Collections is a entity/container which is used to store group of Objects..
--> Collections framework means set of classes and interfaces.

Collections
=============

collections is a framework
Framework means ready made software
Collections is called as framework because it is providing predefined interfaces, classes and methods to perform operations on data.

Example:
78788787878982928
shorting this array ----> Collections.sort(num);

                            ========================================
                                    Collections hierarchy
                            ========================================

1.Iterable(super interface)
2.Collections(interface)
3.List(Interface)
4.Set(Interface)

5.Map(Interface)   ---- > separate family



List: It is used to store group of objects.( Duplicates are allowed )

                1. ArrayList
                2. LinkedList
                3. Vector
                4. Stack

Set: It is used to store group of objects.( Duplicates are not allowed )
                
                1.HashSet
                2.LinkedHashSet
                3.TreeSet
Queue: It is used to store group of objects. ( FIFO--First In First Out )

                1.PriorityQueue

Map: It is used to store group of objects.( Key-Value pair )
                
                1.HashMap
                2.LinkedHashMap
                3.HashTable
                4.TreeMap
                5.IdentityHashMap
                6.WeakHashMap


